div.p:
Now, it really looks like a website, doesn’t it? <h1> is a heading tag in HTML (the biggest size), while <p> is an HTML paragraph (i.e. normal text). <a> is the hyperlink tag and href= specifies the URL, in this case: a Wikipedia article. As attributes often contain extra information about the element that you don't want to appear in the actual content, the texts "Go to Wikipedia page of Ramesses VI" is displayed in place of the lengthy URL (
                            https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramesses_VI
                        ).
